"{\"uid\": \"wired.com-story-jesse-grupper-gear-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"In the pastfew years, sport climbing has become one of the fastest-growing sports in the world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 95, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This explosion in popularity could be because of superstars like Alex Honnold, who in addition to starring in the documentaryFree Solonow has several climbing shows withNational Geographic.\", \"from\": 97, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 162, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Honnold\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Honnold\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Honnold\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Honnold\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It could also be the proliferation of easily accessible indoor gyms.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Or maybe it's just because sport climbing is the safer way to go up a wall; its competitors clip ropes into secure, pre-drilled bolts rather than setting their own protective equipment the way traditional, or trad, climbers do.\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport made its Olympic debut at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, with climbers matching up in three different formats: speed, lead, and bouldering.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"US climber Nathaniel Coleman secured a gold medal in the men's combined event at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 0.999997474531034, \"rank\": 2.5254726805304766e-06, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}, {\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Coleman\", \"score\": 0.9999991758226073, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nathaniel Coleman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Coleman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This August, American Jesse Grupper will be competing in Paris.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999977808754077, \"rank\": 2.2191214266790833e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6901796978314001e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Grupper is from Montclair, New Jersey, where he started climbing in an indoor gym when he was six.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 0.9999999936253516, \"rank\": 6.370862659315888e-09, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He earned his degree in mechanical engineering from Tufts and worked inHarvard's Biodesign Lab, developing exoskeletons for stroke victims, and he is currently still a research fellow in the lab.\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Grupper largely pivoted away from the academic research life when he went full-time pro and started cleaning up on the World Cup competition circuit.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023, he qualified for the 2024 Paris Olympics when he took gold in the men's combined lead and bouldering in Santiago at the2023 Pan American Games.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"score\": 0.9999999980809662, \"rank\": 1.7761196082816948e-09, \"text\": \"Santiago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I caught up with Jesse over Zoom on a sunny training day in Switzerland to find out what he's bringing to Paris.\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1555, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.999999416652997, \"rank\": 5.811695029964053e-07, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6901796978314001e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you buy something using links in our stories, we may earn a commission.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This helps support our journalism.Learn more.\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"JLab Audio  Amazon  Walmart  Best Buy  Over Zoom, I kept finding myself peering at Grupper's earbuds to find out what he had.\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were the JLab Go Air Sport, which is the top-ranked budget option in ourBest Headphones for Working Outguide.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are the sport version of 2020's Go Air (8/10, WIRED Recommends) that cost just a little bit more for the secure ear hooks and a cover that closes on top.\", \"from\": 1972, \"to\": 2130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2009, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Go_First\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Go Air\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q46970\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Go_First\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Go_First\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The build quality, Bluetooth connection, and sound quality are amazing, considering the price.\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a plus, they come in a wide variety of playful colors.\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They fit easily, they are not too expensive,\\\" Grupper says.\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have had them for a while, and they are not broken yet, so I am excited about that.\\\"\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"REI  Amazon  Backcountry  La Sportiva is an Italian company that's been making technical climbing apparel for almost 100 years.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2442, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime_Video\", \"score\": 0.8056766195256114, \"rank\": 0.22760004117775132, \"text\": \"Amazon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime_Video\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime_Video\"}, {\"begin\": 2463, \"end\": 2474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Sportiva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Sportiva\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Sportiva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Sportiva\"}, {\"begin\": 2481, \"end\": 2488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9883701885709198, \"rank\": 0.010860393922976611, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When you are choosing between closure systems on your climbing shoes, laced closures will give you a more fine-tuned fit, while Velcro lets you get them on and off more easily.\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2693, \"end\": 2699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Velcro\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.974981410655119e-13, \"text\": \"Velcro\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Velcro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Velcro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Solution combines the two with La Sportiva's Fast Lacing system.\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2777, \"end\": 2788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Sportiva\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Sportiva\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Sportiva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Sportiva\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As with all footwear, finding the exact right climbing shoe can be a challenge-and even more so for professional climbers, who rely on their precision footwork to get ever higher.\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These have that nice middle point of being flexible enough to stand on volumes [the climbing term for bigger surfaces] while still being stiff enough for tiny footholds,\\\" Grupper says.\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 3177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A lot of companies have moved toward creating softer shoes for the indoor market, but I like having a stiffer shoe for my quiver.\\\"\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amazon  Armaid  In the past few months, Grupper has been dealing with a flexor tendon strain; earlier this year, he had to take a six-week break to allow his hands to recover.\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3313, \"end\": 3319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime_Video\", \"score\": 0.8056766195256114, \"rank\": 0.22760004117775132, \"text\": \"Amazon\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime_Video\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime_Video\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was stressful, he says, though he is maintaining a positive attitude as Paris gets closer.\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3564, \"end\": 3569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6901796978314001e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not feel like I have to compare myself to others, or want to do that, because I am just trying to figure out where I am at.\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not in the best physical shape of my life, and that might change in the next month, but I am just trying to take it day by day.\\\"\", \"from\": 3713, \"to\": 3846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Armaid is a small, portable device that lets you massage trigger points-small, pressure-sensitive areas that can carry a lot of pain and stiffness.\", \"from\": 3848, \"to\": 3999, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Armaid consists of a nonskid base, a stationary arm, and an adjustable small arm with small roller balls.\", \"from\": 4000, \"to\": 4109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I put my forearm right in here and squeeze with my other hand so my forearm is compressed,\\\" Grupper says, demonstrating.\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The tendon that I sprained runs all the way through my forearm, so I can release it from the tension.\\\"\", \"from\": 4232, \"to\": 4335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Armaid is also helpful for other overuse injuries, like tennis elbow, golfer's elbow, or tendinitis.\", \"from\": 4336, \"to\": 4440, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Trango  Most climbers do not need too many features on their harness.\", \"from\": 4444, \"to\": 4513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unless the climber is competing in a specific discipline like ice climbing or canyoneering, or if they have a specific body type-children typically require a kid's harness, for example-then they can just pick a harness based on comfort.\", \"from\": 4514, \"to\": 4750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I sit in my harness a lot of the day when I am training, so comfort is probably the most important thing I look for in a harness,\\\" Grupper says.\", \"from\": 4751, \"to\": 4896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He uses the Trango Horizon.\", \"from\": 4897, \"to\": 4924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It has extra loops for attaching things to it, it's intuitive to use, and it's a safe brand that I trust.\\\"\", \"from\": 4925, \"to\": 5032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Full disclosure: Trango is one of Grupper's sponsors and the representation that arranged this interview.\", \"from\": 5033, \"to\": 5138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sterling  When you are climbing, your rope is your best friend.\", \"from\": 5142, \"to\": 5205, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the item that keeps you from falling and hitting the ground!\", \"from\": 5206, \"to\": 5271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are many different kinds of ropes, but for sport climbing, you want a single, dynamic rope that will stretch and give as you fall.\", \"from\": 5272, \"to\": 5408, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A thicker rope is more durable, but harder to carry and maneuver into the draws.\", \"from\": 5409, \"to\": 5489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also, keep your rope's length in mind-you want the pitch that you are climbing to be half the length of your rope in order to descend safely.\", \"from\": 5490, \"to\": 5631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So if you are climbing a 30-meter route, you need a 60-meter rope.\", \"from\": 5632, \"to\": 5698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grupper likes Sterling's Aero Rope because, with a thickness of 9.2 millimeters, it's extremely thin and light compared to other ropes.\", \"from\": 5700, \"to\": 5835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5714, \"end\": 5722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8283509132933584e-45, \"text\": \"Sterling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fibers are also treated with what Sterling callsa Xeros processthat keeps it clean and dry and allows it to glide more easily through your rappel or belay device.\", \"from\": 5836, \"to\": 6002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5874, \"end\": 5882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8283509132933584e-45, \"text\": \"Sterling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also easier to slide it through draws so your rope is not creating unnecessary drag.\", \"from\": 6003, \"to\": 6092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The higher you go, the more weight that's strapped onto your harness,\\\" he says.\", \"from\": 6093, \"to\": 6173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sterling's ropes are vetted by the ecological responsibility certification group Bluesign, and the company has a recycling program for dead ropes-a nice option if you do not feel likehooking your own rugout of your spent ropes.\", \"from\": 6174, \"to\": 6401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6174, \"end\": 6182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8283509132933584e-45, \"text\": \"Sterling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pound_sterling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finish Line  JD Sports  \\\"My gear has changed a decent amount due to climate change,\\\" Grupper says.\", \"from\": 6405, \"to\": 6503, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As with most outdoor sports, cooler air temperatures are preferable.\", \"from\": 6504, \"to\": 6572, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grupper likes climbing when it's around 50 to 60 degrees Fahrenheit.\", \"from\": 6573, \"to\": 6641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6630, \"end\": 6640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8759669692400072e-56, \"text\": \"Fahrenheit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fahrenheit\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, this year in Paris, the temperatures are expected to rise quite a bit higher, possibly reaching90 degrees.\", \"from\": 6642, \"to\": 6763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6670, \"end\": 6675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6901796978314001e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When temperatures are high, most of us stay safe by staying in temperature-controlled environments and not exerting ourselves too heavily.\", \"from\": 6765, \"to\": 6903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's not an option for Olympians, who are justly concerned about thehealth risksof competing in high temperatures.According to a 2023 report, 110 athletes suffered heat-related illnesses during the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 6904, \"to\": 7119, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's number could be even higher.\", \"from\": 7120, \"to\": 7160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Almost every competitor has a personal fan, and a lot of teams bring ice packs and coolers.\", \"from\": 7162, \"to\": 7254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We might have personal air conditioners for the warm-up area itself,\\\" which is indoors, while the venue is outside, says Grupper.\", \"from\": 7255, \"to\": 7384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do think it's pretty interesting how the sport is evolving to meet the demands of climate change.\\\"\", \"from\": 7385, \"to\": 7486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily, most of the teams are providing personal cooling equipment, but Grupper has been practicing while wearing an ice vest, just to see what it feels like.\", \"from\": 7488, \"to\": 7647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nike has made specific ice vests for Team USA for this year's Olympics; this is not one, but it has four refreezable ice packs in pockets that can be easily transported.\", \"from\": 7648, \"to\": 7817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7648, \"end\": 7652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.9999997872637549, \"rank\": 2.1273629611324062e-07, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}, {\"begin\": 7685, \"end\": 7693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.207076875511917e-13, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sometimes I will even pour water on my head before competing,\\\" Grupper says.\", \"from\": 7819, \"to\": 7896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I may not look my best, but it's what you have to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 7897, \"to\": 7952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grupper will be competing in the men's bouldering and lead competitions at theLe Bourget climbing venue.\", \"from\": 7954, \"to\": 8058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first semifinal will be held on August 5, and the men's final will be held on August 9.\", \"from\": 8059, \"to\": 8150, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In your inbox:Will Knight'sAI Labexplores advances in AI  'Flying cars'will take off this summer  Big Story:InsideOpenAI's raceto catch up to Claude Code  How'Handala'became the face of Iran's hacker counterattacks  Listen:Nvidia's 'Super Bowl of AI,' and Tesla disappoints  Squarespace Promo Code: 20% Off Annual Acuity Subscriptions  LG Promo Code: 20% Off Your First Order  10% Off Dell Coupon Code for New Customers  30% Samsung Coupon - Offer Program 2026  10% Off Canon Promo Code + Up to 30% Off  50% Off Doordash Promo Code for New & Existing Users  More From WIRED  Reviews and Guides  \\u00a92026Cond\\u00e9 Nast.\", \"from\": 8152, \"to\": 8763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8206, \"end\": 8208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999735373425, \"rank\": 2.646258017708764e-08, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 8338, \"end\": 8342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5812762830463031, \"rank\": 0.7202959086131612, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 8375, \"end\": 8381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nvidia\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nvidia\"}, {\"begin\": 8399, \"end\": 8401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999735373425, \"rank\": 2.646258017708764e-08, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}, {\"begin\": 8408, \"end\": 8413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\", \"score\": 0.9999780235052799, \"rank\": 2.1976830964822502e-05, \"text\": \"Tesla\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\"}, {\"begin\": 8427, \"end\": 8438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Squarespace\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Squarespace\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Squarespace\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Squarespace\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.WIREDmay earn a portion of sales from products that are purchased through our site as part of our Affiliate Partnerships with retailers.\", \"from\": 8764, \"to\": 8920, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The material on this site may not be reproduced, distributed, transmitted, cached or otherwise used, except with the prior written permission of Cond\\u00e9 Nast.Ad Choices\", \"from\": 8921, \"to\": 9087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9066, \"end\": 9071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis,_Grand_Cond\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.7069136048505587, \"rank\": 0.19609582963625774, \"text\": \"Cond\\u00e9\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis,_Grand_Cond\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis,_Grand_Cond\\u00e9\"}]}]}"